{
  "text": "Consider a message on the edge connecting function node to variable node . Let denote the message sent along the edge from variable node to function node . Also, let denote the message sent along the edge from function node to function node . Further, let denote the set of all the neighbors of node and let indicate the summary operator. A summary operator summarizes a function for a particular set of variables. For example consider a function , then a possible summary operator could be the summation operator in (5) [CITATION_1] With this notation, the message computations performed by the sum-product algorithm can be expressed as follows in (6) and (7):",
